 the Irrua Reference Laboratory for the test. He pointed out that the four confirmed cases who had since been placed on self-isolation have been evacuated to the Niger Delta University Teaching Hospital, NDUTH Isolation Centre, where they will be managed and closely monitored. Dr. Nathaniel further revealed that other samples including that of the health worker who provided direct clinical care to the index case tested negative. He said: ” All the contacts of the confirmed cases will adequately line listed and followed up including necessary environmental decontamination. Samples will be collected from their high-risk contacts while risk communication and community engagement will continue unabated as usual.” vanguard The Kaduna State Commissioner for Health, Dr. Amina Baloni, on Saturday, confirmed one new case of coronavirus in the state Baloni, who disclosed this at a press briefing in Kaduna,  said the new case is a close contact of one of the three active cases announced earlier in the week.… April 25, 2020 In "News" ADO-EKITI—THE Ekiti State government, yesterday, confirmed the death of an American, who died of the Corona virus. It also disclosed the  positive case of the virus in a patient in the State. March 19, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" LAGOS—Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, said yesterday that every state of the federation would have its share of coronavirus. April 17, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates"